7095 silly resolved     readme: '# is-obj [![Build Status](https://travis-ci.org/sindresorhus/is-obj.svg?branch=master)](https://travis-ci.org/sindresorhus/is-obj)\n\n> Check if a value is an object\n\nKeep in mind that array, function, regexp, etc, are objects in JavaScript.<br>\nSee [`is-plain-obj`](https://github.com/sindresorhus/is-plain-obj) if you want to check for plain objects.\n\n\n## Install\n\n```\n$ npm install --save is-obj\n```\n\n\n## Usage\n\n```js\nconst isObj = require(\'is-obj\');\n\nisObj({foo: \'bar\'});\n//=> true\n\nisObj([1, 2, 3]);\n//=> true\n\nisObj(\'foo\');\n//=> false\n```\n\n\n## License\n\nMIT © [Sindre Sorhus](https://sindresorhus.com)\n',
